	This fascinating wooden candle holder is made from twigs in the shape of a pentagram and has a glass tea-light holder in the centre. This decorative candle holder would make the perfect addition to any room in the house including living rooms and bedrooms or would be excellent to be used on a personal altar. It would also make the perfect gift idea for someone who is a lover of hand-crafted, natural items and candles or just likes what pentagrams represent. The pentagram was used in ancient times as a Christian symbol for the five senses. It became popular as a magic symbol, attributing the five neoplatonic elements to the five points, in typical Renaissance fashion. This decorative wooden pentagram candle holder measures 21cm wide and 7cm tall.</p>
